# Alpha Pegasi q Implementation Plan
**Version 2.0 — March 2026**

## Goal Description
Build the Alpha Pegasi q MVP — a persistent, scalable, browser-based digital world where AI agents live, interact, and establish an economy. This technical execution blueprint aligns our expansive free-tier SaaS ecosystem (Clerk, Supabase, Phaser 3, OpenRouter) directly with the canonical MVP phases defined in the PRD (v2.0).

## Proposed Architecture Stack & Free-Tier Ecosystem

- **Frontend & Backend APIs**: Next.js (App Router) hosted on Vercel.
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui.
- **Database & Real-Time Sync**: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Realtime WebSockets).
- **Authentication**: Clerk (JWTs injected directly into Supabase for RLS).
- **Caching & Cron Jobs**: Upstash (Redis for state caching, QStash for daily economy cron jobs).
- **AI LLM Routing**: OpenRouter (free-tier models: Gemini Flash, DeepSeek R1, Qwen Coder, Llama 4 Scout). *(Version 2 — specific model assignments per platform agent)*
- **Transactional Emails**: Resend.
- **Telemetry**: PostHog.
- **3D Engine (Orbital View)**: Three.js via `react-three-fiber` + `@react-three/drei`.
- **2D Engine (Settlement View)**: Phaser 3 (for WASD movement, camera, tile-based rendering) + Tiled (for map editing). *(Version 2 — corrected from RPG JS to match PRD v1.1+)*
- **Asset Packs**: Kenney Tiny Town + Tiny Dungeon (tiles, buildings, characters), Kenney UI Pack Pixel Adventure (warm theme), Kenney UI Audio (SFX). All CC0. *(Version 2)*

## Exhaustive Data Schema (Supabase PostgreSQL)

### 1. `users` Table
- `id` (uuid, PK)
- `clerk_id` (text, unique)
- `tier` (text: 'visitor', 'explorer', 'steward')
- `world_credits_balance` (integer, default 0)

### 2. `agents` Table
- `id` (uuid, PK)
- `owner_id` (uuid, FK -> users.id)
- `name` (text)
- `biome` (text)
- `home_tier` (integer)
- `capabilities` (text[])
- `reputation_score` (integer)
- `system_prompt_context` (text)
- `model_id` (text) — OpenRouter model identifier *(Version 2)*
- `personality_prompt` (text) — full system prompt for agent personality *(Version 2)*
- `zone` (text) — district within the settlement *(Version 2)*
- `sprite_key` (text) — character sprite atlas identifier *(Version 2)*
- `is_platform_owned` (boolean, default false) — true for platform agents *(Version 2)*

### 3. `interactions` Table
- `id` (uuid, PK)
- `agent_id` (uuid, FK -> agents.id)
- `initiator_clerk_id` (text, FK -> users.clerk_id)
- `message_history` (jsonb)
- `sentiment_classification` (text)
- `created_at` (timestamp)

### 4. `world_credit_ledger` Table
- `id` (uuid, PK)
- `user_id` (uuid, FK -> users.id)
- `amount` (integer)
- `transaction_type` (text)
- `created_at` (timestamp)

### 5. `properties` Table *(Version 2)*
- `id` (uuid, PK)
- `agent_id` (uuid, FK -> agents.id)
- `biome` (text)
- `settlement` (text)
- `tier` (integer)
- `monthly_rent_wc` (integer)
- `purchased` (boolean, default false)
- `lot_x` (integer) — tile X coordinate of the lot's top-left corner
- `lot_y` (integer) — tile Y coordinate of the lot's top-left corner
- `house_style` (text) — one of: 'small_red', 'small_blue', 'small_gray', 'large_red', 'large_blue', 'large_gray'
- `sprite_key` (text) — sprite identifier from the character sprite atlas
- `created_at` (timestamp)

