## Phased Execution Strategy (Aligned with PRD MVP Definition)

### Phase 0 — Foundation
**Scope:** Project scaffolding. Next.js + Three.js setup. Database schema. Authentication. Deployment pipeline.
- Initialize Next.js (App Router) and deploy to Vercel.
- Configure Clerk for authentication (Visitor, Explorer, Steward).
- Set up Supabase PostgreSQL. Define tables and Row Level Security (RLS) linked via Clerk JWTs.
- Establish centralized error logging and foundational UI (Tailwind GUI).

### Phase 1 — The Planet
**Scope:** 3D rotating sphere. 15 biome regions visible. Day/night cycle. Zoom transition.
- Implement Three.js canvas with `SphereGeometry`.
- Write custom GLSL shaders to texture the 15 biomes and render the day/night terminator line (synced to server time via Supabase).
- Implement smooth camera pan/zoom into the Arboria biome trigger zone.

### Phase 2 — Arboria
**Scope:** 2D pixel-art regional map. Top-down WASD settlement. Weather. Three demo agents.
- Integrate the open-source **Phaser 3** engine.
- Use **Tiled** to visually design the Arboria settlement map (tiles, collision, lighting).
- Hook up Supabase Realtime to broadcast live weather (rain, mist) down to the Phaser 3 client.
- Place 3 static demo NPCs in the Phaser 3 map with interactive prompt boundaries.

### Phase 2.5 — Arboria Visual Reimagining *(Version 2)*
**Scope:** Replace all placeholder art with production-quality Kenney pixel art. Expand agent roster. Add ambient world population. Implement claimable lot system. Audio. UI reskin.

**Visual Assets & Map**
- Replace placeholder tileset with Kenney Tiny Town `tilemap_packed.png` (16x16 tiles, CC0).
- Redesign Arboria Market Town map in Tiled: 64x64 tiles (up from 50x50), 5 named districts (Town Gate, Market Square, Scholar's Quarter, Craftsmen's Row, Commons Park).
- Build combined character sprite atlas (`characters.png` + `characters.json`) from Kenney Tiny Town + Tiny Dungeon character pools.
- Replace player sprite and all NPC sprites with unique, visually distinct Kenney characters.

**Platform Agents (3 → 5)**
- Expand from 3 demo agents to 5 platform agents: Mira (guide), Ledger (finance), Archon (academia), Forge (programming), Ember (roleplay).
- Assign each agent a specific free-tier OpenRouter model: Gemini Flash, Gemini Flash Lite, DeepSeek R1, Qwen Coder, Llama 4 Scout.
- Write personality system prompts for each agent with world-aware context injection.
- Replace seed migration `0006_seed_agents.sql` with new `0007_platform_agents.sql`.

**Ambient NPCs (12)**
- Implement `ambientNpcManager.ts` — 12 non-AI NPCs with static positions, idle animation, and proximity-triggered speech bubbles.
- Each NPC has 3 pre-written lines referencing agents, biomes, credits, and seasons.
- No name labels, no "Press E" prompts — visual distinction from AI agents.

**Claimable Lots (18)**
- Implement `lotManager.ts` — runtime tile patching system for Steward-claimed lots.
- 18 empty lots (5x5 tiles each) distributed across districts, rendered as fenced grass with signposts when unclaimed.
- On scene load, query `properties` table and patch tilemap layers with claimed house tiles and agent sprites.

**Audio**
- Implement `audioManager.ts` — load Kenney UI Audio SFX in BootScene.
- 7 trigger types: proximity chime, panel open/close, button click, message received, hover, NPC bubble pop.
- Global mute toggle persisted in localStorage. Default volume 30%.

**UI Reskin**
- Re-skin settlement HUD, interaction prompts, and breadcrumb with Kenney UI Pack Pixel Adventure (warm/parchment theme).
- Design chat overlay and agent registration UI components (implemented in Phases 3 and 4 respectively).

### Phase 3 — Agent Interaction
**Scope:** Text conversation with agents. Interaction memory. Sentiment classification. Agent status.
- Build the React Chat UI overlay (pixel art themed per Phase 2.5 design) that opens when interacting with a Phaser 3 NPC.
- Construct the `Agent Communication Protocol` server-side API Gateway.
- Proxy prompts through OpenRouter, dynamically injecting `world_state` (weather/time) and historical `interactions` (memory) retrieved from Supabase.
- Store the new conversation logs and LLM sentiment analysis securely in DB.

### Phase 4 — Economy & Accounts
**Scope:** Stripe integration. World Credits. Steward account. Agent registration. Recommendations.
- Build the Agent Registration Flow (Next.js forms) with sprite picker, house style picker, and lot selector (pixel art themed per Phase 2.5 design). *(Version 2)*
- Wire up Stripe webhooks to increment the user's `world_credits_balance` in Supabase.
- Build Upstash QStash cron jobs to deduct property base rent daily.
- Develop the "Biome Recommendation" engine logic.

### Phase 5 — Polish & Launch
**Scope:** Performance optimization. Mobile responsive shell. Admin panel.
- WebGL profiling; assure Three.js maintains 60fps and Phaser 3 culling optimizes memory.
- Wrap the UI gracefully for mobile touchscreen playability.
- Build the internal Platform Governor Admin interface (reading directly from Supabase).
- Deep security audit of RLS policies before soft launch.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Manual Verification
- **Framework Readiness**: Validate token pass-through from Clerk to Supabase and ensure RLS blocks unauthorized writes.
- **Performance Profiling**: Use Chrome DevTools to ensure the Three.js canvas and Phaser 3 instances are heavily optimized.
- **Agent Sandbox Testing**: Write server-side unit tests for the Agent Gateway to ensure prompts are properly hydrated and APIs hidden.
- **Economy Integrity**: Test Stripe webhook idempotency and QStash chron triggers.
